        <p>Schematic representation of the recurrence intervals between two concurrently active motor units. Each discharge from one motor unit is used as a reference point to determine forward and backward latencies to the discharges of the second motor unit. The first order intervals are the latencies to the first forward and backward discharges (noted in red). The second order are the second forward and backward discharges (noted in purple).</p>
      </caption>
